UNITED STATES of America v. Mary Fry DAWSON, Appellant. No. 14887. United States Court of Appeals Third Circuit. Argued Jan. 17, 1966. Decided Feb. 15, 1966. William D. Morgan, Scranton, Pa., for appellant. Carlon M. O’Malley, Jr., Asst. U. S. Atty., Scranton, Pa. (Bernard J. Brown, U. S. Atty., Scranton, Pa., on the brief), for appellee.

Before KALODNER, Chief Judge, and McLAUGHLIN and GANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM:

On review of the record we find no error. The Judgment of the sentence will be affirmed.
